WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:31.960 --> 00:00:37.060
The Dai ethnic group lives in south-eastern China's Yunnan Province.

00:00:37.060 --> 00:00:44.500
Each year they hold a grand festival called
the Water-Splashing Festival (po shui jie).

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:59.640
People dressed in beautiful clothes sing dance
and splash water on each other

00:00:59.660 --> 00:01:02.200
on the morning of the festival.

00:01:15.160 --> 00:01:20.500
Don't get angry if you are drenched; 
it represents a blessing.

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:24.160
More water means more
good luck in the coming year.

00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:45.500
If a young man receives pouches made by a girl that means the girl has fallen in love with him.

00:01:56.620 --> 00:02:00.920
Po shui jie is regarded as the Valentine's
Day for the Dai ethnic group.

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:06.180
Po shui jie has become part of the culture
in Yunnan Province.

00:02:06.700 --> 00:02:14.000
Nowadays, not only Dai people but also tourists
participate in this exciting carnival.

